text: Maly Buzat () is a rural locality (a village) in Buzatovsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 50 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 44 km from Sterlibashevo, 3 km from Buzat. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Maly Buzat
